(from, g));\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        // Queenside castling\r\n        if (board.canCastleQueenSide(colour)) {\r\n\r\n            Position b = new Position(1, row);\r\n            Position c = new Position(2, row);\r\n            Position d = new Position(3, row);\r\n// makes sure those squares are empty and don't go into check\r\n            if (board.getPiece(b) == null &&\r\n                    board.getPiece(c) == null &&\r\n                    board.getPiece(d) == null &&\r\n\r\n                    !CheckDetector.isSquareAttacked(board, d, colour) &&\r\n                    !CheckDetector.isSquareAttacked(board, c, colour)) {\r\n\r\n                moves.add(new Move(from, c));\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    ","comment":""}},{"from":"MoveValidator","to":"CheckDetector","kind":"uses","label":"משתמש ב‑CheckDetector (בגוף הפונקציה)","fld":null,"mth":{"v":"+","ret":"boolean","n":"isLegalMove","p":"board, move, turn","ctor":false,"body":"\r\n// checks if a piece and if the right colour of it has been selected\r\n        Piece piece = board.getPiece(move.from);\r\n        if (piece == null) return false;\r\n\r\n        if (piece.getColour() != turn) return false;\r\n//fills up the list with generated moves\r\n        List<Move> pseudoLegal = MoveGenerator.generateMoves(board, move.from);\r\n        // checks if the move is in the list\r\n        if (!pseudoLegal.contains(move)) return false;\r\n\r\n        //  CASTLING THROUGH CHECK saftey\r\n        // makes sure it's a castle\r\n        if (piece.getType() == PieceType.KING &&\r\n                Math.abs(move.to.x - move.from.x) == 2) {\r\n\r\n            //if in check it can't perform\r\n            if (CheckDetector.isKingInCheck(board, turn)) {\r\n                return false;\r\n            }\r\n// checks castling direction\r\n            int dir = (move.to.x > move.from.x) ? 1 : -1;\r\n\r\n            //  Square the king passes through must be safe\r\n            //so creates the middle